.TH DCR-BUILD 1 "2026-06-02" "dcr 0.7.0" "DCR Manual"
.SH NAME
dcr-build \- Compile a DCR project
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dcr build
[\fB\-\-debug\fR | \fB\-\-release\fR]
[\fB\-\-target\fR \fI<triple>\fR]
[\fB\-\-force\fR]
[\fB\-\-clean\fR]
[\fB\-\-verbose\fR]
[\fB\-\-workspace\fR \fI<name>\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compiles the project. Default profile is \fB\-\-debug\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Build with debug profile (default). Enables debug symbols.
.TP
.B \-\-release
Build with release profile. Enables full optimization.
.TP
.B \-\-target \fI<triple>\fR
Cross-compile for the given target.
.TP
.B \-\-force
Force a full rebuild, ignoring cached artifacts.
.TP
.B \-\-clean
Clean before building.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Print detailed build output including compiler commands.
.TP
.B \-\-workspace \fI<name>\fR
Build a specific workspace member.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dcr (1)
